				<cite class="fn">picobit</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=988&amp;cpage=1#comment-3626">October 12, 2012 at 8:03 am</a></div>

		<p>This is a really, really bad idea.  Remember, you can only check your bitcoins after you receive them, and then it is too late.</p>
<p>Imagine going to the ATM, and withdraw 200$.  Too bad, 120 of them have traces of cocaine (or are black, as you mention above), and are therefore not accepted by honest merchants.</p>
<p>In the bitcoin world: You buy a load of bitcoins on an exchange.  Unfortunately, the guy selling them to the exchange got them from a guy who got them from a girl, who got them from a guy, who &#8230; &#8230; &#8230; who was a scammer and had all his coins tainted.  Tough luck!  If such a system would become widespread, noone would dare use bitcoins as money.</p>
<p>The problem you are attempting to address is very, very real, and badly need a solution.  But taint is the obvious solution that has been discussed and rejected countless times.</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/?p=988&#038;replytocom=3626#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-3626", "3626", "respond", "988")'>Reply</a>		</div>
